definition:
Someone descended from Shaul who was a man of the tribe of Simeon living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.10; 
 son of: Simeon (H8095) and Canaanite_woman (H3669); 
 brother of: Jemuel (H3223), Jamin (H3226), Ohad (H0161), Jachin (H3199) and Zerah (H2226L); 
 father of: Shallum (H7967K)
Group of sha.ul (שָׁאוּל "Shaul" H7586H) 
 § Shaulites, of Saul "desired"
 descendants of Saul or Shaul
